The paper discusses the use of Evolutionary Algorithms in Intrusion Detection Systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the modeling of the problem into ES primitives, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The fitness evaluation of the population involves the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the generation of rules for IDS, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
